data.enText: likely to be good or successful

data.chText: 我们公司的前景一片光明。
data.enText: The future is looking very rosy for our company.

data.chText: 她把他们在意大利的共同生活描绘得非常美好。
data.enText: She painted a rosy picture of their life together in Italy (= made it appear to be very good and perhaps better than it really was) .
everything in the garden is rosy
everything in the garden is rosy

example: she made a fortunate decision to go to medical school

tr: having the pinkish flush of health

example: looked at the world through rose-colored glasses

value.def: If you say that someone has a rosy face, you mean that they have pink cheeks and look very healthy.

example.ex: Bethan's round, rosy face seemed hardly to have aged at all...
example.tran: 贝唐红扑扑的圆脸看起来似乎一点也没有变老。

value.def: Something that is rosy is reddish-pink in colour.
If you say that a situation looks rosy or that the picture looks rosy, you mean that the situation seems likely to be good or successful.

example.ex: Little over a year ago, things looked very rosy for the Social Democrats...
example.tran: 一年多以前，社会民主党人的形势看起来一片大好。

example.ex: The job prospects for those graduating in engineering are far less rosy now than they used to be...
example.tran: 现在那些工科毕业生的工作前景大不如从前。

example.ex: Is the picture really so rosy?

value.tran: 充满希望的;前景美好的;有望成功的

trans: 彩霞；彩云；红霞；红霞万朵
